Usage:

    btty [N]

Provides access to virtual terminal associated with /dev/ttyN, default N is 1.
Useful for starting Xwindows via ssh, for example.

All key codes are passed verbatim except '^]' which exits the program.

^L is passed to the virtual terminal, but also triggers a redraw of the local
screen.

Note you may need to set the client $TERM to match your screen's $TERM.
